items.title: Block out the noise and stay invested — stock picks and advice from one of the world’s oldest mutual funds
items.description: Since launching in 1934, The Investment Company of America fund has rolled with world war and evolving economies. These are its stock picks.

items.title: Social Security will stop sending paper checks soon. How to make sure you still get your benefits on time.
items.description: Paper Social Security checks will be eliminated on Sept. 30.

items.title: Global stocks fall, oil futures rise, on a report U.S. may soon strike Iran
items.description: Asian and European stocks fell on Thursday, and oil futures rose, as reports suggested a U.S. military strike against Iran could happen this weekend.

items.title: Jamie Dimon wants workers in the office. So why is he letting JPMorgan’s European chief work remotely?
items.description: The return-to-office double standard has sparked a conversation online: “Rules for thee but not for me.”

items.title: ‘Everybody is in danger’ as budget cuts gut caregiving services
items.description: Labor activist Ai-jen Poo, featured in Bradley Cooper’s PBS “Caregiving” documentary, says “the story of caregiving in America is everyone’s story.”
